text.tspan: Fig 2: Replace example CL_DUT with our version
cl_AWS_BSV_Top.sv is a hollowed-out version of cl_dram_dma.sv
The blue boxes are our BSV code, most of which are instantiations or
small variants of existing BSV code in WindSoC.
AXI.64.512 is an instantiation of the BSV AXI4 fabric IP for 64b addrs
and 512b data (AWS' natural width for DDR4s and AXI4 interfaces).
The 4 slaves connect directly to the AWS DDR4s
1 master connects directly to AWS DMA_PCIS interface.
'Mem Adapter' is a variant of the WindSoC Mem_Controller, where the
front end has 64b addrs and data (as in WindSoC and GFE SoCs)
and the back end has 512b data connecting to Fabric_2x4.
The AXI4L.32.32-to-AXI4.64.64 is a bit of ad hoc logic so that reads
and writes on the AWS OCL bus (AXI4-Lite) are converted into
memory accesses in DDR A via Fabric_2x4. Only this piece is
"throwaway"; all the other pieces will be used for the GFE.
The 'C Tests' code combines the C code from test_dram_dma_hw_sw_cosim
- Does DMA transfers in both directions to each of the 4 DDRs
(and checks the data), using the DMA_PCIS port (AXI4.64.512)
- Does peeks and pokes to DDR A via the OCL port (AXI4-Lite.32.32)
